# Clear Writing Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p3g1qe"
longer sentences
=
better writing
```

or:

```text id="u7g6qe"
grammar
=
punctuation
only
```

Some may:

```text id="c9g4qe"
write
sentence fragments
```

without understanding:

```text id="k4g7qe"
sentences
need
complete ideas
```

Students may also:

```text id="n1g8qe"
create
run-on sentences
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="t6g2qe"
ideas
need
clear structure
```

Example:

student writes:

```text id="q8g3qe"
Because
I was late.
```

and treats it as:

```text id="v5g9qe"
complete sentence
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="a7g4qe"
fragment
```

because:

```text id="g2g6rx"
complete sentences
need
subject
and
predicate
```

Another example:

student writes:

```text id="w1g5rt"
I ran home
I forgot
my lunch
```

instead of revising:

```text id="j6g8qe"
I ran home
because
I forgot
my lunch.
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="n9g3qe"
clarity through structure
```

